oai_dc:dc.dc:title: BLOCK SUBSIDENCE UNDER PRESSURE AND FLOW
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Sakai, T.
Gotoh, H.
Yamamoto, T.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: block subsidence
pressure
armor
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The block subsides gradually into sandy bed under water pressure fluctuation. In actual coast the oscillatory flow also acts on the block. The block subsidence is reproduced qualitatively in a laboratory. The subsidence occurs even under the oscillatory flow. Under some combinations of water pressure fluctuation and oscillatory flow, the subsidence is larger than any of the subsidence under the pressure fluctuation only and the subsidence under the oscillatory flow only.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 24 (1994): Proceedings of 24th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Kobe, Japan, 1994.
